article.description: Damni Applewhite had 10 points and 12 rebounds to carry South Carolina State to a 63-54 win over Maryland Eastern Shore in the Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference Tourney first round on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Applewhite lifts SC State past Md.-Eastern Shore 63-54
article.linkText: Applewhite lifts SC State past Md.-Eastern Shore 63-54
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Damni Applewhite had 10 points and 12 rebounds to carry South Carolina State to a 63-54 win over Maryland Eastern Shore in the Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference Tourney first round on Tuesday night. Janai Raynor-Powell had 15 points for South Carolina State (8-25). Jahmari Etienne added 10 points. Bryan Urrutia had 14 points and six rebounds for the Hawks (7-25). Isaac Taylor added 12 points. Ryan Andino, the Hawks' leading scorer heading into the contest at 10 points per game, shot only 19 percent in the game (3 of 16). --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
